{'push_id': 9626367388, 'size': 4, 'distinct_size': 4, 'ref': 'refs/heads/virtio', 'head': 'd333e99c48439e7ce842ca64d33888277b359353', 'before': '625c1259b5ec2675797cfb6c231d84440039575b', 'commits': [{'sha': 'ed0bf6ec851cdc453e4b5fa12d9492c4eba4afc7', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': "pci: Update dm_pci_bus_to_virt() parameters

Add mask parameter and reorder length parameter to match the other PCI
address conversion functions. Using PCI_REGION_TYPE as the mask gives
the old behaviour.

It's converted from a macro to an inline function as the length
parameter is now used twice, but should only be calculated once.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>", 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/ed0bf6ec851cdc453e4b5fa12d9492c4eba4afc7'}, {'sha': '5faa60732c3fd807a5838eb519e70d706fcd7883', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'pci: Add mask parameter to dm_pci_map_bar()

Add a mask parameter to control the lookup of the PCI region from which
the mapping can be made.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/5faa60732c3fd807a5838eb519e70d706fcd7883'}, {'sha': 'dbaeb0b77c3a9c65b0ac8f10d96ef3f9efe7c3d8', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'virtio: pci: Check virtio configs are mapped

Prepare for calls to `virtio_pci_map_capability()` failing by returning
NULL on error. If this happens, later accesses to the pointers would be
unsafe so cause the probe to fail if such an error occurs.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/dbaeb0b77c3a9c65b0ac8f10d96ef3f9efe7c3d8'}, {'sha': 'd333e99c48439e7ce842ca64d33888277b359353', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'virtio: pci: Make use of dm_pci_map_bar()

The virtio PCI capabilities describe regions of memory that should be
mapped. Map those with dm_pci_map_bar() which will ensure they are valid
PCI regions.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/d333e99c48439e7ce842ca64d33888277b359353'}]}

{'push_id': 9624193268, 'size': 18, 'distinct_size': 18, 'ref': 'refs/heads/virtio', 'head': '625c1259b5ec2675797cfb6c231d84440039575b', 'before': 'e26ae4d0cd508cf6267e1fe3fe287ed5a6b796b8', 'commits': [{'sha': 'f5c18a98001622aaa9b7f3df916fe2c1731446e0', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'virtio: pci: Allow exclusion of legacy driver

Add a new config to control whether the driver for legacy virtio PCI
devices is included in the build. VIRTIO_PCI_LEGACY is included by
default when VIRTIO_PCI is selected, but it can also be independently
toggled.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/f5c18a98001622aaa9b7f3df916fe2c1731446e0'}, {'sha': 'f2d8d831b057bad294b6b8d71fdf3a0540a27b95', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'virtio: pci: Fix discovery of device config length

The length of the device config was erroneously being taken from the
notify capability. Correct this by finding the length in the device
capability.

Fixes: 550435edf810 ("virtio: pci: Support non-legacy PCI transport device")
Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/f2d8d831b057bad294b6b8d71fdf3a0540a27b95'}, {'sha': '11dd5c5dee479dfa48986ac566b8b5273a0a037f', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'virtio: pci: Bounds check device config access

The device config is optional, so check it was present and mapped before
trying to use the pointer. Bounds violations are an error, not just a
warning, so bail if the checks fail.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/11dd5c5dee479dfa48986ac566b8b5273a0a037f'}, {'sha': 'b6748cf2e081a62ec6037cec137e327491debf2e', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'virtio: pci: Bounds check notification writes

Make sure virtio notifications are written within their allocated
buffer.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/b6748cf2e081a62ec6037cec137e327491debf2e'}, {'sha': '143d56e56432b073a0e2dd6eb344fe8bd0bc1073', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'virtio: pci: Check virtio common config size

Check that the common config is at least as large as the struct it is
expected to contain. Only then is it safe to cast the pointer and be
safe from out-of-bounds accesses.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/143d56e56432b073a0e2dd6eb344fe8bd0bc1073'}, {'sha': '2f76d315f6124bdbdbc8da42edbd5716ed2e7f96', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': "virtio: pci: Check virtio capability is in bounds

Ensure the virtio PCI capabilities are contained within the bounds of
the device's configuration space. The expected size of the capability is
passed when searching for the capability to enforce this check.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>", 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/2f76d315f6124bdbdbc8da42edbd5716ed2e7f96'}, {'sha': 'd171a3bff7f7736990c586808f2b84a8d1e683ac', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'virtio: pci: Read entire capability into memory

Read the virtio PCI capability out of the device configuration space to
a struct rather than accessing fields directly from the configuration
space as they are needed. This both makes access to the fields easier
and avoids re-reading fields.

Re-reading fields could result in time-of-check to time-of-use problems,
should the value in the configuration space change. The range check of
the `bar` field and the later call to `dm_pci_read_bar32()` is an
example of where this could happen.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/d171a3bff7f7736990c586808f2b84a8d1e683ac'}, {'sha': 'df5a4020ea73f3d3c8c1fb5eeafd6ab34a9bfa30', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'pci: Fix use of flags in dm_pci_map_bar()

The flags parameter of dm_pci_map_bar() is used for PCI region flags
rather than memory mapping flags. Fix the type to match that of the
region flags and stop using the regions flags as memory mapping flags.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/df5a4020ea73f3d3c8c1fb5eeafd6ab34a9bfa30'}, {'sha': 'a3e63e1e0a6935b7e91dd6d25df8515b32fca1b7', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'pci: Add config for Enhanced Allocation

Add a config to control whether Enhanced Allocation is supported by the
driver.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/a3e63e1e0a6935b7e91dd6d25df8515b32fca1b7'}, {'sha': 'c265df401549f6000866ddfd4bf08d207e329397', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'pci: Check region ranges are addressable

When parsing the `ranges` DT node, check that both extremes of the
regions are addressable without overflow. This assumption can then be
safely made when processing the regions.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/c265df401549f6000866ddfd4bf08d207e329397'}, {'sha': '01ddc3975e19fd8059d44002560f461c67498b84', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'pci: Range check address conversions

When converting between PCI bus and physical addresses, include a length
parameter that can be used to check that the entire range fits within
one of the PCI regions. This prevents an address being returned that
might be only partially valid for the range it is going to be used for.

Where the range check is not wanted, passing a length of 0 will have the
same behaviour as before this change.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/01ddc3975e19fd8059d44002560f461c67498b84'}, {'sha': '39f0a9c337c45ee751d527e47db9d0da4469d693', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'test: pci: Test PCI address conversion functions

Add tests for the functions dm_pci_bus_to_phys() and
dm_pci_phys_to_bus() which convert between PCI bus addresses and
physical addresses based on the ranges declared for the PCI controller.

The ranges of bus#1 are used for the tests, adding a translation to one
of the ranges to cover more cases.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/39f0a9c337c45ee751d527e47db9d0da4469d693'}, {'sha': '2437bb2bbd3f6b68c3c37962c6aec7151084488d', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'pci: Map bars with offset and length

Evolve dm_pci_map_bar() to include an offset and length parameter. These
allow a portion of the memory to be mapped and range checks to be
applied.

Passing both the offset and length as zero results in the previous
behaviour and this is used to migrate the previous callers.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/2437bb2bbd3f6b68c3c37962c6aec7151084488d'}, {'sha': '685c29c2b5527375b16b5fb20416deb21a56a953', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': "pci: Match region flags using a mask

When converting addresses, apply a mask to the region flags during
lookup. This allows the caller to specify which flags are important and
which are not, for example to exclude system memory regions.

The behaviour of the function is changed such that they don't
preferentially search for a non-system memory region. However, system
memory regions are added after other regions in decode_regions() leading
to a similar outcome.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com", 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/685c29c2b5527375b16b5fb20416deb21a56a953'}, {'sha': 'd71b37705119455adee73faee47ab534db90ee7b', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': "pci: Update dm_pci_bus_to_virt() parameters

Add mask parameter and reorder length parameter to match the other PCI
address conversion functions. Using PCI_REGION_TYPE as the mask gives
the old behaviour.

It's converted from a macro to an inline function as the length
parameter is now used twice, but should only be calculated once.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>", 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/d71b37705119455adee73faee47ab534db90ee7b'}, {'sha': '44e452923dfda1e4d412a76d26b506f1e38f99e0', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'pci: Add mask parameter to dm_pci_map_bar()

Add a mask parameter to control the lookup of the PCI region from which
the mapping can be made.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/44e452923dfda1e4d412a76d26b506f1e38f99e0'}, {'sha': '38c088f8e2d2c8ef28fc8e23a736912e8c1992bf', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'virtio: pci: Check virtio configs are mapped

Prepare for calls to `virtio_pci_map_capability()` failing by returning
NULL on error. If this happens, later accesses to the pointers would be

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/38c088f8e2d2c8ef28fc8e23a736912e8c1992bf'}, {'sha': '625c1259b5ec2675797cfb6c231d84440039575b', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'virtio: pci: Make use of dm_pci_map_bar()

The virtio PCI capabilities describe regions of memory that should be

PCI regions.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Bin Meng <bmeng.cn@gmail.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/625c1259b5ec2675797cfb6c231d84440039575b'}]}

{'push_id': 9616917190, 'size': 8, 'distinct_size': 8, 'ref': 'refs/heads/vring', 'head': '09d3dc147c41ca004ee90b0fc366db36a91e1e3c', 'before': 'f39089aede25e7d906cb6d2d13bf27a17e9dddf9', 'commits': [{'sha': '5fedbea23483ed40dd7e8dbd8ce1812afe5052bf', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'dm: test: virtio: Test the virtio ring

The virtio ring is the basis of virtio communication. Test its basic
functionality and its resilience against corruption from the device.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Simon Glass <sjg@chromium.org>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/5fedbea23483ed40dd7e8dbd8ce1812afe5052bf'}, {'sha': 'f98d467e5d744290627249d9c1ce58395973e57e', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'virtio: sandbox: Fix device features bitfield

The virtio sandbox transport was setting the device features value to
the bit index rather than shifting a bit to the right index. Fix this
using the bit manipulation macros.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Simon Glass <sjg@chromium.org>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/f98d467e5d744290627249d9c1ce58395973e57e'}, {'sha': '35bde53fe0ed2dd51f0bf9a871fa6f6d5b97debe', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': "test: dm: virtio: Test notify before del_vqs

The virtqueue is passed to virtio_notify() so move the virtqueue
deletion to the end of the test when it's no longer needed. This wasn't
causing any problems because the sandbox virtio transport driver doesn't
do anything for notifications, but it could cause problems if things
change and it was a bad example.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Simon Glass <sjg@chromium.org>", 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/35bde53fe0ed2dd51f0bf9a871fa6f6d5b97debe'}, {'sha': 'd0cc1965ad23b413a3ad078ecd55befbaaf5a758', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'test: dm: virtio: Split out virtio device tests

Virtio tests that find a child device require the virtio device driver
to be included in the build so it can probe. The sandbox virtio
transport driver currently reports a virtio-blk device so make sure the
corresponding driver is built before running tests that need it.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/d0cc1965ad23b413a3ad078ecd55befbaaf5a758'}, {'sha': '4e0b9d5ee97ea04a9fe5e21f076565b5bc6fb753', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'virtio: sandbox: Bind RNG rather than block device

The virtio-rng driver is extremely simple, making it suitable for
testing more of the virtio uclass logic. Have the sandbox driver bind
the virtio-rng driver rather than the virtio-blk driver so it can be
used in tests.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Simon Glass <sjg@chromium.org>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/4e0b9d5ee97ea04a9fe5e21f076565b5bc6fb753'}, {'sha': 'c2e3d8a7359ccd0e7f88d91d18a5de405fce7179', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'test: dm: virtio: Test virtio device driver probing

Once the virtio-rng driver has been bound, probe it to trigger the pre
and post child probe hooks of the virtio uclass driver. Check the status
of the virtio device to confirm it reached the expected state.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Simon Glass <sjg@chromium.org>', 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/c2e3d8a7359ccd0e7f88d91d18a5de405fce7179'}, {'sha': 'd9fe5c057932b4e8267c2c6c016a62d22f89c175', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': "virtio: rng: Check length before copying

Check the length of data written by the device is consistent with the
size of the buffers to avoid out-of-bounds memory accesses in case
values aren't consistent.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Scull <ascull@google.com>
Cc: Sughosh Ganu <sughosh.ganu@linaro.org>
Reviewed-by: Simon Glass <sjg@chromium.org>", 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/AndrewScull/u-boot/commits/d9fe5c057932b4e8267c2c6c016a62d22f89c175'}, {'sha': '09d3dc147c41ca004ee90b0fc366db36a91e1e3c', 'author': {'email': 'ascull@google.com', 'name': 'Andrew Scull'}, 'message': 'test: dm: virtio_rng: Test virtio-rng with faked device

buffer if the virtio device provides an invalid length.
